MY
DEAR
JEAN:

This
card,
this
picture
that
you
addressed,
I
hardly
know
who

Was

really
you

did

wish
me
to
seek
your

veritable
face?
Jean,
I
want
to
see
you
again.
I
hunt
for
you
every

where.
I
remember,
and
search
furiously
through
the
years
as
if

to
find
a
flower,
a
friend,
a
key.

You
watched

surrounded

in
a
mirror.

It
rained
and

gay.
